f(x) = \ln\left(1-\frac{1}{x^2}\right)
f(2)+f(3)+f(4)=\ln\left(\frac58\right)
f(2)+f(3)+f(4)=\ln(3/4)+\ln(8/9)+\ln(15/16)
\ln(5/8)
f(x)=\ln\left(1-\dfrac1{x^2}\right)=\ln\left(\dfrac{x^2-1}{x^2}\right)
\Rightarrow f(2)=\ln\left(\dfrac34\right)\quad f(3)=\ln\left(\dfrac{8}{9}\right)\quad f(4)=\ln\left(\dfrac{15}{16}\right)
\begin{align}f(2)+f(3)+f(4)&=\ln\left(\dfrac34\right)+\ln\left(\dfrac{8}{9}\right)+\ln\left(\dfrac{15}{16}\right)\\ & \overset{\mathbf{Pr. 1}}{=} \ln\left(\dfrac34\cdot\dfrac{8}{9}\cdot\dfrac{15}{16}\right)\\ &=\ln\left(\dfrac58\right). \end{align}
